          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0403P0_20030408_CWS_4' title='Link to this speech by Mrs Barbara Roche' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mrs-barbara-roche" title="Mrs Barbara Roche">The Minister for Social Exclusion and Deputy Minister for Women (Mrs. Barbara Roche)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">In my written Statement on Friday 4 April, I announced that we would be making available &#x00A3;800 million to local authorities from the Neighbourhood Renewal Fund (NRF) in 2004&#x2013;05 and 2005&#x2013;06 as part of our strategy to revitalise England's poorest neighbourhoods and create places where people want to live, not leave.</p><a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_11ws' title='Col. 11WS &mdash; HC Deb 08 April 2003 vol 403 c11WS' name='column_11ws' href='#column_11ws' rel='bookmark'>11WS</a><p>I am today announcing the details of individual allocations for each of the 88 local authorities that are eligible for NRF. These are set out in the table below.</p><p><table>
